title: L Canarsie Tunnel Reconstruction Public Workshops
body: March 1,  2017Dear Subscriber:The Metropolitan Transportation Authority (MTA) and the New York City Department of Transportation (NYCDOT) held two public workshops to discuss possible travel alternatives to L subway service in preparation for the 2019 closure of the Canarsie Tunnel. Two more workshops are scheduled. Input from the meetings will inform the ongoing studies and traffic modeling exercises.Last Thursday,  customers gathered at Our Lady of Guadalupe,  and,  the week before that,  at the Williamsburg High School for Architecture & Design to hear presentations,  discuss service options,  and provide feedback to officials from the MTA and NYCDOT.  Participants engaged in interactive discussions about how they currently use the transit system and how their trips may change during the closure.  Information received at the workshops will be considered as representatives develop alternative service plans for when the tunnel is closed for reconstruction. We welcome your participation in the two remaining workshops:East Williamsburg6:00 PM - 8:00 PMThursday,  March 2,  2017Progress High School850 Grand Street,  Brooklyn,  NY 11211Manhattan Eastside7:00 PM - 9:00 PMThursday,  March 9,  2017Town and Village Synagogue334 East 14th Street,  NY,  NY 10003We'll keep you updated on important project milestones and our planning as the process moves forward.  We invite you to view new pages on the MTA website at: http://web.mta.info/sandy/PlanningServiceAlternatives.htmThank you, L Line Canarsie Tunnel Reconstruction Project Team                          3/1/17 3:03 PM             NYC

title: UPDATED: BKLYN, N Trains, Track Work and Construction
body: Due to ongoing track work and construction between 8 Av and 86 St,  the following service changes are in effect: Southbound [N] trains are running on the D line making all stops from 36 St (Bklyn) to Coney Island-Stillwell Av. As an alternative,  customers can take the F or R train into Brooklyn or take a N  train to 62 St-New Utrecht or Coney Island Stillwell Av and transfer to a Manhattan-bound N train. For additional station by station travel alternatives click here: http://web.mta.info/nyct/service/N_ConeyIsland.htmlFree Shuttle buses are running from 36 St (Bklyn) to Coney Island-Stillwell Av. Transfer between N  trains and Shuttle buses at: 36 St (Bklyn) D,  N,  R ,  62 St-New Utrecht Av D,  N  and Coney Island-Stillwell Av D,  F,  N,  Q.
